<h2>Heading Styles</h2>

<h1>Heading level 1</h1>   
<p>This is a paragraph of text. It should be styled according to the CSS rules defined in the project.</p>

<h2>Heading level 2</h2>
<p>Another paragraph of text, under a level 2 heading.</p>

<h3>Heading level 3</h3>
<p>And another paragraph, under a level 3 heading.</p>

<h4>Heading level 4</h4>
<p>And another paragraph, under a level 4 heading.</p>

<h5>Heading level 5</h5>
<p>And another paragraph, under a level 5 heading.</p>

<hr />

<h2>Lists</h2>
<p>Unordered lists should look like this:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Unordered list item 1</li>
    <li>Unordered list item 2</li>
    <li>Unordered list item 3</li>
</ul>

<p>Ordered lists should look like this:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Ordered list item 1</li>
    <li>Ordered list item 2</li>
    <li>Ordered list item 3</li>
</ol>

<p>Definition lists should look like this:</p>
<dl>
    <dt>Definition term 1</dt>
    <dd>Definition description 1</dd>
    <dt>Definition term 2</dt>
    <dd>Definition description 2</dd>
</dl>

<p>Blockquotes should look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
    <p>This is a blockquote. It should be styled according to the CSS rules defined in the project.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Links should look like this: <a href="https://www.example.com">Example Link</a></p>

<hr />

<h2>Code Examples</h2>

<p>Here is some inline code: <code>const x = 10;</code></p>

<p>And here is a code block:</p>
<pre><code>function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}</code></pre>

<hr />

<h2>Forms</h2>

<p>Forms should look like this:</p>
<form>
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" />

    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" />

    <button type="submit">Request a free trial</button>
</form>

<hr />
<h2>Buttons</h2>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Primary Button</button>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--secondary">Secondary Button</button>
<br>
<a href="#" class="btn btn--primary">Primary Link Button</a>
<a href="#" class="btn btn--secondary">Secondary Link Button</a>
<br>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--primary btn--sm">Small Primary Button</button>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--secondary btn--sm">Small Secondary Button
<br>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Large Primary Button</button>
<button type="button" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg">Large Secondary Button